🔹 Basic File & Directory Commands

    ls → List files and directories
    pwd → Show current directory path
    cd <dir> → Change directory
    mkdir <name> → Create a new directory
    rmdir <name> → Remove empty directory
    rm <file> → Delete file
    rm -r <dir> → Delete directory recursively


🔹 File Viewing & Editing

  cat <file> → Display file contents
  less <file> → View file page by page
  nano <file> → Open simple text editor
  touch <file> → Create empty file


🔹 File Management

  cp <src> <dest> → Copy files
  mv <src> <dest> → Move or rename files
  chmod → Change file permissions
  chown → Change file ownership

🔹 System & Process Commands

  top → View running processes (live)
  ps → Show current processes
  kill <PID> → Stop a process
  df -h → Show disk usage
  free -h → Show memory usage

🔹Networking Commands

ping <host> → Test network connection
ifconfig / ip addr → Show network info
wget <url> → Download files from internet
curl <url> → Fetch data from a URL

🔹 Package Management (varies by distro)
   On Ubuntu / Debian:
       sudo apt update
       sudo apt install <package>

    On Fedora / CentOS:
        sudo dnf update
        sudo dnf install <package>

🔹 Helpful Tips
   Use man <command> to read the manual
   Use --help with most commands for quick usage
   Press Tab for auto-completion
   Use arrow keys to navigate command history



